caption: I’ve been here several times, and always had a great experience. The Croque Madame is amazing. Breakfast burrito is great. We always get the home fries, so crispy and yummy. The deluxe breakfast sandwich is incredible. Mac and cheese is soooo good. Always a great time. Love coming here!!! Staff is always really nice.

I took a photo of the RVC salad I bought the other day because it was so beautiful. The staff is so nice!! The food is amazing!! Their breakfast mac & cheese!?! I wish they sold it by the pound. 10/10, always an amazing experience.

I ordered a small catered breakfast for the morning of my wedding. Madison was wonderful in helping me pick out some items and everything arrived so fresh and on time. There was still plenty left over for us newlyweds to enjoy the next morning too. The breakfast pastrys and granola parfaits where a big hit especially. I will definitely be using The Flour Shoppe Cafe in the future and will highly recommend to everyone i know.

From the quality of service down to the food, it was absolutely fine dining! My husband and I went in for brunch. He had a bacon burger and I had a classic breakfast platter which both entries were very good. The portions were just right. I highly recommend👌🏾.
It’s a nice cute spot. Food was good, it hit the spot.  Good customer service.  They should try adding mimosas to the menu tho
Small hole in the place with delicious food
excellent food & good, friendly service. Small digs but cozy.  only criticism is get the food to stay, to go is not as good or as much!
Had some of the best brunch food around and a killer espresso too!
Awesome food and service. Their coffee is also amazing. The only downside was that the space inside was a little tight but other than that I love this place.

Me and my friends were looking for a place to sit indoors because all the places in Manhattan were outdoor dining. We traveled from the city to check out this place. We were able to sit where we wanted but had to go to the register to place our order and the waiter brought over the food to us. None of us really enjoyed the food but the water. Three adults and one child. I felt the food was rushed and not seasoned well. And I ate a half done raw burger! I was really hungry so I went with the burger and added salt, pepper, ketchup and it already had bbq sauce so it made it more tasty. I didn’t notice how raw the burger was until my friend ask “you eat your food that way”? And I said what you mean and she pointed out the half done cooked burger. I should of took it back to them and ask for a fully cooked burger which I would of thought they would of asked how I wanted it done but I just let it go and decided to write this review and took photos. And they were about to close so we didn’t bother because my friend said his burger was the same because he noticed it but said he didn’t want to make a fuss. I know some people eat their food this way and I didn’t want to waste it but I shouldn’t have eaten it my stomach was messed up right after. The cashier and waiter seemed nice but the service of giving us a raw burger made me give them two stars. I will not be going back and don’t recommend because the food that we ordered wasn’t tasty.

The place is tiny and very popular it seems, so be prepared to wait for a table.  The staff was all around 10 stars!  Friendly, patient & quick on there toes.  The food was fresh and everything tasted great.
Still has great coffee, high-quality food and moderately high prices.
When I say I love this place, I LOVE THIS PLACE. The food is amazing.
I enjoyed the service that I was served.
I had the banana crumb pancakes.  Oh my , wow. They were unbelievable. Run, don't walk to this place.  I will be returning for sure.
If you have 2 hours to wait for your food go to this restaurant

Loved the outdoor dining experience at this cute cafe! I would definitely recommend ordering their Banana Crumble Pancakes, they’re super delicious with just the perfect amount of sweetness. The staff is very friendly, organized, and clean!

Food is 7/10 and I think that's good, especially for my scoring. Tiny location but generally good service. Here is my big caveate - Madison not only drop the ball in a key moment, she threw it in my face. I called and email with interest to do catering and she didn't follow through or up. When I followed up after hours of waiting, she hung up on me. Called back - my call was ignored. 😏. Now I have to improvise last minute after inquiring for over a week. It's my wife BDay event. I will figure it out but I'm grateful Madison displayed her character. This allows me to avoid doing business with folks that don't care. Thank you again.
Stopped by in a pinch, amazing food and big portions! Had the Deluxe Breakfast Sandwich and it was so delicious! Worth every penny, excited to eat here again!
My now, Fiancé, & I had brunch there yesterday! GOOOD food! 😋😋 Thank you again for the engagement cookies!!

Arrived at 11:50 a.m I was told 25 minute wait. After 40 minutes I was told again 25 minutes.  Didnt get seated til 1:10 pm. Ordered food at 1pm while waiting didn't get served til 1:40pm. I was with my daughters and staff was very disorganized.  Food looked better than it taste. Came for the kit kat croissant and they were sold out. Mind you we got there at 11:50am. Smh. Would not recommend.  Bad experience all around

I am surprised that after all this time you guys haven’t gotten your act together yet!  After waiting an hour when it was a half hour wait. We were seated a table that felt like we would roll down the hill or at least our food would roll off the table. In understand outdoor dining can be tricky but at least level the table so people can sit comfortably.  I gave in my order and when the drinks came one water instead of 2 , no straws, no stirers for the coffee. The food came and again no salt pepper etc... they never came back to bring it and by that time the food was cold. So we went in to get salt pepper etc, there is no jelly... what?! Everything should have been brought out together on a tray  all at once.. Everyone was in the phone helping takeout orders They should be a designated person doing outdoor and one to do take out.. Get your act together A most unenjoyable brunch was had by all!!!

I order the Flour Shoppe Breakfast sandwich via Doordash and it was the MOST disgusting sandwich I've ever tasted IN MY ENTIRE LIFE.  I requested for 4 fried eggs and they sent me yolk dripped eggs and the eggs tasted like carton substitutes from Elementary school.  MY FIRST AND LAST TIME PERIOD!!
I just enjoyed their dishes. I always get good customer service here. The place is clean and the workers are always super nice. Will visit here again.
Great spot! Great food. Highly recommend.

Amazing people, Danish are off the chain!!! The omlettes are weird and we got attacked by a bee whilst dining outside.  Not really a breakfast joint.  Come get your danish and a strong man coffee with an expresso shot... whooo!

A little more pricey than competing breakfast options nearby, but the quality of the food is top notch.  The Jelly donuts are always fresh, stuffed with jelly and delicious.  The breakfast items like the croque madam, breakfast poutine and regular breakfast sandwich are on point, the chef makes things the right way from scratch and you can really taste the difference.
(Translated by Google) Excellent food and flavor ...  (Original) Excelente comida y sabor...

Sandwich I ordered was great and made how I requested. They even brought the food outside to me so I wouldn't have to re-enter the store. I was made to feel very comfortable and confident that I was safe doing business here.

I took a photo of the RVC salad I bought the other day because it was so beautiful. The staff is so nice!! The food is amazing!! Their breakfast mac & cheese!?! I wish they sold it by the pound. 10/10, always an amazing experience.

Great little coffee shop. For a small place there is great variety of coffee, some food options, and plenty of dairy alternatives. Service is always quick and friendly and the ambiance is clean and inviting.

The whole grab a menu, get a chair then go back up to order caught me off guard, but I enjoyed it. Gives the employees more time to focus on the quality of the food; which I have to say was delicious! I had a large coffee with vanilla and soy milk to start. Fantastic Stumptown coffee. Then I ordered the banana crumb pancakes with a side of over easy eggs. Yum-me!!! Stuffed me to the core. Totally coming back to try everything else on the menu.

The menu is good but not very vast. They seem to change it often which is good. When there was seating it was weird ordering first then sitting. Seating is kind of crowded. Overall its a good place to visit.
Yummy!!!
Always great. Wish the expanded for more seating. Can get packed on weekends.

Closes early but can always rely on them for consistently good food. Something here for everyone in the mainstay menu, coffee (seems to have recently changed from Stumptown to Jim's Organic), weekly specials and daily rotation of pastries and other baked goods. The baked goods in baskets above the pastries are especially stellar, particularly their croissants and jelly doughnuts. Come early for a chance to grab some and more variety. They know how to keep things exciting.  Before coming and ordering: 1. Check online for updates on weekly specials! Online access to menu pricing as it turns out they offer online orders for pickup (pastries and baked goods aren't available online) or delivery (GrubHub). They do events as well! 2. Upon entering, scope out what's available inside and above the display case. We nabbed up the last 2 doughnuts close to noon. 3. Take a menu and find yourself a seat to contemplate options. 4. Ready? Head up to register to order. 5. Sit + wait for made-to-order food.
Great food and so much choice. It's pretty small so can get very crowded depending on when you go.

small cozy coffee and bakery shop that smells amazing once you walk in. the atmosphere is super welcoming and staff make you feel at home. the coffee is perfect and the food is quite satisfying. never disappointed when i come here.

Food was  very good, I guess that explains the wait. ... just a little pricier than expexted but is definitely worth visiting.

Confused at its glory. We decided to visit the quaint cafe because of it reviews and several people we knew who raves about the delicious food.  I must say the look of the cafe was very nice for a not so convenient area to be in. The tables and stools were a bit sticky but still stayed for the food. Went with my two kids and we were not the least bit impressed. Is it better than the diners in the area perhaps but we have had better food and definitely better coffee and hot chocolate. My daughter ordered a soda which was poured into a plastic cup with a lid fine until she noted what looked like a gnat stuck on the inside of the lid. We didn’t want to make a scene about it so we just left it alone no mention of it. The coffee was more like diner coffee nothing with real flavor and the hot cocoa was more like hot milk. Again lacking flavor we thought this cute cafe would deliver. The food was pretty much the same. The presentation alone is definitely a four or five star presentation but between the taste and flavor rapidly reduced our desire to come back. The people were very friendly which brought up the rating in my eyes thought we won’t be heading back anytime soon.

This rating is weighed down heavily by the extremely poor level of service at this establishment. The FOOD really is AWESOME! If you have all the time in the world and the patience of a saint with an entire morning to spare, by all means enjoy! However, for the majority of us, the experience won't be that enjoyable. I ordered ahead of time for pickup and wasn't given a timeline for when the food would be ready. Given it was a two item breakfast order, I assumed the "We'll see you soon" meant "Be read shortly". As soon as I walked in, I knew I was in for trouble. The front-house staff moves at a snail's pace with ZERO urgency to serve the customers. There's no defined system of who is next. Line forms where? During the 30-40 minutes I stood waiting for food, I observed people ordering at the counter ahead of those who were there before them, an agitated man complaining how long his To-Go order was taking, only for the server to bring it out on a tray to dine-in,  another customer bring in a wrong order delivered to his table saying it was the THIRD TIME they gave him the wrong thing. WHAT!? Close down the restaurant for a few days, retrain your staff, create better systems for ordering and efficient delivery of food, and become the great food spot you intended to be because the food really was excellent but completely overshadowed by an abysmal front of house performance.
Great food. Great to be back home.

I've been going to The Flour Shoppe since its inception and I've experienced the food and service throughout two different ownerships. I originally rated it 5 stars since this was by far the best brunch outside of NYC and the service was extremely friendly plus, together with the music and the decor, it provided one of the best dining experiences in LI. I've since notched it down one star because the food quality has decreased, the service is not as friendly as it used to be, and the restaurant is now extremely crowded with long waits in the weekends. I still come here, but not near as often as I used to. If you want a pleasant experience, try to avoid their busy times.

The café has great ambiance. Going there on a Sunday early enough is a great idea as the place can get filled quickly. It is nicely decorated. The latte is okay but the hot chocolate is terrific! The food we ordered unfortunately was not what was expected. The egg white omelette was good but I did not enjoy the taste of turkey, it had a strong chicken flavor and the spicy sauce did not compliment it well. The buttermilk biscuit sandwich had delicious ham and the eggs were nicely over easy but the biscuit itself was messy and had a pepper like taste that wasn’t very pleasant. The staff was kind but definitely needed a more welcoming attitude and service, specially when we asked what they would recommend and the girl who answered seem a bit uninterested in being of any assistance. Lastly the home fries are terrific and the portions provided are great. May try it again, we did see an order of pancakes that looked delicious!
